	   <tr><td colspan=2>Since Luclin is due to be released within the next week or so , I was wondering , what do yall think about the " New " spells that the cleric class is currently listed to Get. <br><br>Celestial Remedy - Heal over Time , 260 hp , 190mana<br>Sermon of the Righteous - Undead Damage over Time , 240 damage , 100mana<br>Sacred Word - AE Stun / DD 90 , 120 mana<br>Armor of the Faithful - Self Only HP AC, 200mana<br>Epitaph of Life - DoT 750 , 275mana<br>Mark of Retribution - Healing Damage Shield , 115mana<br>Judgement - DD 750 , 325mana<br>Blessed Armor of the Risen - Self only HP AC / MANA Regen 275 mana<br>Blessings of Aegolism - Group Aego , 2000mana<br><br><br>Currently the feeling that I am getting from these spells, is that we really aren't getting anything new , just a few spells that I call Learner spells , basically spells that are downgrades to spells that we currently have , for those that have yet to get them , giving them a smaller leaerning curve on the new type of spells that other clerics pre Luclin didn't have. <br><br>For those clerics that have already reached the level 60 mark , unfortunately the only thing that I see that they would be getting that would be usefull, would be the Blessed Armor of the Risen , and the Blessings of Aegolism . <br><br>Granted their is the new list of level 51+ skills that can be learned that is supposedly coming out , and when luclin is released, I'll make note of those as well , but currently the spell list appears to be stable than the skills list , so its what I commented on first. <br><br><br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Dytren Lang<br>Sacrosanct Legion<br>The Rathe</td></tr>
