	   <tr><td colspan=2>Well, so far I have used Armor of the Faithful and Epitaph of Life. I have some of others but being 52nd level, I can't use them yet.<br>Armor of the Faithful: Very useful. It stacks with SOW and Hero line of spell so additional AC and HP have been a life saver for me a couple of times. Now I can have 3 buffs on me other than symbols and have over 2000 hp and almost 700 in AC.<br>Epitaph of Life: Great spell for using on undead. They do 700+ damage (I think max is 750) very quickly, about 30 sec RT. Very nice to add to the melees to finish up quickly. For example, on Coteried Centurion or Legionnairs, I was able to land 3 of them on each battle with couple of melee types. One downside, they do cause more aggro than other DOTs because of the short time it takes to finish out the damage. Got aggroed a few times after casting two of them. Just stay a bit far away and if the mob is snared, you can just run from it. <br>Good luck with the new spells. <br><br>Taushar<br>&nbsp;<br>Taushar, Tunare Cleric of 52nd plateau<br>Chishar, Druid of 13th plateau<br>Xev Server</td></tr>
