<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100698228148954></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100698228148954><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=5410&mid=100698228148954>Mobs, stuns and roots</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=5410&mid=100698228148954#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=33019><span id= >Alainia</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Nov 28th 4:18 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I agree that keeping the Enchanter alive is extreamely important. I always symbol the enchanter and the main tank with my best symbol spell. The others I use my Symbol of Marzin (group symbol) which gives only 450 hit points, but is MUCH easier on my mana and spell components.<br><br>I usually use the Stun and Stun command if I see the enchanter getting hit.  I don't usually use the stun with push, since the melees seem to get confused when the mob their beating on suddenly moves.<br><br>I do have root memorized however.  Sometimes the enchanter is pancking and running away from the mob, and I'll try to stun then immediately root the mob that's scaring them.  I also use root if a mob is coming after me and gets his smelly breath on me and my clothes.<br><br>As far as healing goes, I have the Complete Healing for the tanks and Diving Light for the pure casters.  I also like celestial healing for healing the hybrids and tanks during battles since it's very mana effecient and I can cast it if there are a lot of mobs around.  I'll sometimes memorize a Group Healing if I want to heal Everyone when their all halfway down in hitponits.  This is usually a rare case however.<br><br>Mark of Karn is a great spell, not only will it heal the melees as their attacking, but it'll overwrite any damage shields the mobs have.  This alone makes Mark of Karn worth memorizing.<br><br>So my spells in an exp group is:<br><br>1.  Complete Healing<br>2.  Divine Light<br>3.  Celestial Healing<br>4.  Stun<br>5.  Stun Command<br>6.  Mark of Karn<br>7.  Root<br>8.  Divine Barrier<br><br>If things are REALLY nasty, I'll replace my Stun with a Divine Aura.<br><br>-- Alainia Tannistar<br>58 Priestess of Tunare<br>Lanys T'Vel<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
