<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100591275492800></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100591275492800><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=5410&mid=100591275492800>RE: General</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=5410&mid=100591275492800#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=5410><span id= >changling the Venerable</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>7 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Nov 16th 7:12 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Aye , I would agree , it is very important for a cleric to understand his group in all aspects and how they can pull aggro , and what needs to be done to counter that. <br><br>I also agree that Complete heal his a very good thing when it comes to dealing with the amount of Hp that full fledged tanks have. However, even with complete heal , Celestial Heal , still has its purposes for the main tanks .  I usually cast Celestial Healing when the tank reaches the 3 bubble mark. This is usually very effective in keeping the tank well out harms range. And then of course you always have Complete Heal for the big massive heal when needed. <br><br>As for spells that I have memmed for healing and group protection. Here is what I currently use , and works very well for me. <br><br>1 - Superior Heal : Mainly used for those instances that Celestial healing just isn't cutting it , but a Complete Heal isn't required. I get some aggro from this spell , but If everyone is doing there job , you should be ok for a single or double cast of this if needed. <br><br>2 - Complete Heal : For any tank that has over 2200 hp , and they are at the 2 bubble mark on the health bar. Usually don't have an aggro problem with this spell, unless I find myself having to cast again to soon. In most of those cases the pull was bad anyways.  <br><br>3 - Celestial Heal : For almost all other types of healing that don't require Superior Heal . Delivers approx 700hp or so , in 3 pulses over a 24 second time period. <br><br>One Great thing that I have noticed is that Celestial Healing will stack with your other heal spells . So in cases where a ranger( or anyone else for that matter ) might need 2 casts of Superior heal , or you can forsee that he will be regaining aggro very shortly after your heal goes off , Cast the Celestial Heal first , followed by Superior Heal . Celestial is in place and working , Superior hits shortly after the first pulse in celestial healing , and the target that was healed , still has 2 pulses of celestial heal left.  This effectively heals 100hp more than 2 superior heals would , and usually has little to no aggro. <br><br>4 - Valor / Reso Line :  I have debated this with a few of my RL friends over and over , but its worked for me VERY well .  Instead of using Greater Heal for healing Casters and Minor Melee classes , use this.  Yes it costs just a small amount more in mana , to heal close to the same amount of HP ,however , because this spell is a BUFF , it doesn't Carry with it the aggro that a heal spell would do, unless its casts multiple Times (ie 4+) .  The only conflict that you will have here , is that the Valor / Reso line of spells does not stack with the Skin Line of spells.  This shouldn't really be an issue , until you have a Level 49+ Druid in the Group because Skin Like Nature , is Better that Reso, however , until Skin Like Nature , the cleric line of Spells are better by 1 or 2 AC .   I know its only a couple of AC , and some druids will argue that point , and still want to use their skin lines , but until SLN the Valor / Reso Line is better, and gives you the cleric an opportunity to control your aggro that much more. <br><br><br>5 - This spell slot varies from situation to situation , sometimes it might be Extinguish Fatique , other times it might be a stun or some other spell. <br><br>6 - The appropriate type Nuke , for whatever we are fighting. I've had people argue this to me as well. And while I do aggree that it is hardly ever used , I keep it up just in case its needed, to drop a mob that is running, and for some odd reason the main nuker is out of mana ( resists whatever ).  <br><br>7 & 8 - Divine Aura and Divine Barrier . The Cleric attempt to get out of Jail Free Card . Lets face it , as much as this fact sucks, there are times when you the cleric , must make the hard choice , of Hitting these, and High Tailing it for the nearest zone line , not because you want to desert your group but because you know that if you die to , its going to take a REALLY REALLY long time to do CR. <br><br>And as a Cleric , Med as much as possible. <br><br>Hope this is of some help , and made sense. <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Dytren Lang<br>Sacrosanct Legion<br>The Rathe</td></tr>
