	   <tr><td colspan=2>I would definately aggree that chanters are most helpful in the line of aggro control ,however they are not always available.  When they are available, in groups that I'm in you will always find them With Reso , AoF , and Symbol up . One of the best ways to keep a chanter alive for those dire needed seconds is to make sure that they have more AC / HP than they normally would. <br><br><br>There have been very few instances that I have found the atone spell to be worth the casting time. The Spell itself is not a mana hog , but the casting time of the spell , makes it not worth it, unless you are able to get a root off on the mob on that you are trying to atone. <br><br>Root vs Stun . My personal preference here, if I wind up having to use them , is root, mainly because root is resisted alot less than the STUN line making it more mana efficient to just toss a root, and then heal whoever was being beat upon as they clear melee range.<br><br>And in regards to aggro , what spells do you as cleric see that cause the most aggro , self or other group member aggro. And I'm not talking about people that overcast, I'm reffering to spells, that when cast in general almost always send the caster to the top of hate list. <br><br>The Main spells that I tend to notice that have this affect are :<br><br>Snare<br>Disease Cloud<br>Mez<br>44 necro nuke ( I don't recall the name ) which turns the NPC into a skeleton.<br>Slow<br><br><br>When I know that one of these spells will be being cast, I know can prepare for that caster to gain aggro for a few seconds, and be ready to cast a minor heal of sorts on that caster, should they indeed obtain aggro. <br>&nbsp;<br>Dytren Lang<br>Sacrosanct Legion<br>The Rathe</td></tr>
