<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100202720027247></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100202720027247><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=journal.html?user=5410&mid=100202720027247>aggro (stun or root)</a> <a id=fs8 href=journal.html?user=5410&mid=100202720027247#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Oct 2nd 8:53 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[4.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I've found, lately, that stun is more effective than root.  Being a cleric in the lowerlevels (sub 35), you notice that not all of the people you group with have any sort of built-up trust in you.  Therefore, say the enchanter gets aggroed...they run like they had just stuck their head in a hornets nest.  In this situation, I would to time my root to hit when the runner was far enough from the group to not aggro.  As I've grown a bit (being 39, almost 40 now), I've come to realize that I do have a bit of a reputation built up, and people do trust in those they are grouping with (for the most part).  Not many people freak out and run, and if they do, it's not likely they'll run far, so any root would potentially damage a groupmate.  If the Enchanter is being hounded, I will stun, giving the Enchanter enought time to stop, and mez the pursuing mob.  If the situation becomes dire, and root has to be used (due to resisted stuns and their slow repop time), make sure to tell the group so that people can move and mez accordingly.<br><br>Overall...Clerics do have a modicum of crowd control ability, but better (IMHO) to ensure the Enchanter stays alive long enough to do what they're best at, and leave the healing to us.<br><br>Thundergut Rumblebelly<br>Shadowclaw<br>Prexus<br><br>P.S.  Not sure if this made sense or not, format is kinda hard to read in this little post box =P<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
